A woman was admitted to hospital after she was shot by suspected thugs in the buttocks at Embakasi on Tuesday night.Police said the woman was walking to her house when she was confronted by a gang riding on a motorbike."They tried to grab her bag but she resisted, prompting them to shoot her once in the buttocks," police said.Police, who have launched a hunt for the suspected criminals, say the gang rode off after the foiled robbery.Separately, a woman died after a tractor crushed her at the Multimedia University in Nairobi, on Tuesday.Read: Two suspected thugs shot dead in Nairobi as crime rate soarsAlso read: Crime rate in Nairobi almost twice national average Ipsos